---
description: Avoid nested call expressions inside method-chain arguments.
globs: **/*.php,**/*.js,**/*.ts,**/*.vue
alwaysApply: false
---

# No Nested Calls in Arguments

Prefer extracting nested call expressions to named variables before passing them into chained calls.

- Do not pass `new Foo(...)->bar()` directly as a method argument.
- Do not pass deep call stacks directly in argument lists when they reduce readability.
- Extract intermediate values to variables with clear names.
- In PHP tests, avoid passing method calls directly to `expect(...)` when a named variable improves readability.
- In validation setup, avoid passing nested request method calls inline (for example in `Validator::make` arguments); extract `rules`, `messages`, and `attributes` first.
- In tests, do not pass `route(...)` inline when used as argument of a chain/call; extract route variables first.
- In tests, do not pass `now()->...`, `sha1(...)`, `encrypt(...)`, `json_encode(...)`, or any call stack inline inside call arguments when assigned variables improve traceability.

## Deterministic enforcement

- If an argument contains `(` and also contains `)->` or nested function calls, extract to variable before call.
- `expect(...)` must receive a variable when the expression contains any method/function call.
- For builders/factories in multiline form, chain calls must be split and intermediate values extracted when used as arguments elsewhere.

```php
// Bad
$service->send(new ReportBuilder($input)->buildHtml());

// Good
$reportBuilder = new ReportBuilder($input);
$reportHtml = $reportBuilder->buildHtml();
$service->send($reportHtml);
```

```php
// Bad
expect($request->authorize())->toBeTrue();

// Good
$isAuthorized = $request->authorize();
expect($isAuthorized)
    ->toBeTrue();
```

```php
// Bad
$response = $this->post(route('login.store'), ['email' => $user->email]);

// Good
$loginStoreRoute = route('login.store');
$response = $this->post($loginStoreRoute, ['email' => $user->email]);
```

```php
// Bad
$verificationUrl = URL::temporarySignedRoute(
    'verification.verify',
    now()->addMinutes(60),
    ['id' => $user->id, 'hash' => sha1($user->email)]
);

// Good
$verificationExpiresAt = now()->addMinutes(60);
$verificationHash = sha1($user->email);
$verificationUrl = URL::temporarySignedRoute(
    'verification.verify',
    $verificationExpiresAt,
    ['id' => $user->id, 'hash' => $verificationHash]
);
```

```php
// Bad
$validator = Validator::make($payload, $request->rules(), $request->messages(), $request->attributes());

// Good
$rules = $request->rules();
$messages = $request->messages();
$attributes = $request->attributes();
$validator = Validator::make($payload, $rules, $messages, $attributes);

// Even better
$validator = Validator::make(
                                $payload, 
                                $rules, 
                                $messages, 
                                $attributes
                            );
```

```ts
// Bad
store.dispatch(actions.save(formatter.normalize(payload).toDTO()));

// Good
const normalizedPayload = formatter.normalize(payload);
const dto = normalizedPayload.toDTO();
store.dispatch(actions.save(dto));
```
